Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.19,0:00:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The most precious moment in life is the time of taking a decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.15,0:00:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.26,0:00:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But also bequeathed to us \Nnumerous lessons on how to live.{unsure, lit is "for the sake of living, precepts, numerous left behind"}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.39,0:00:31.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,700)\c&H0007DF&\fs100\b1\bord0\blur1}Animentary\N{\b\c&HE0DBF3&}Decision
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.41,0:00:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Wisdom is your weapon{honestly no clue what is megurase here, deepl says "rack one's brain"}\NRemember to use your head{智恵をめぐらせ 頭を使え}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.33,0:00:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave all your worries aside, \NIf you are a man{悩み抜け抜け 男なら}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.95,0:00:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,One decision is enough \NTo make others cry or laugh{泣くも笑うも 決断ひとつ}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.86,0:01:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If you win, don't get your nose high, \NIf you lose - don't cry{勝っておごるな 敗れて泣くな}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.69,0:01:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, don't you ever let other see your tears{男 涙は見せぬもの}
Comment: 0,0:01:34.91,0:01:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{ch}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.74,0:01:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,December of 1941.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.57,0:02:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to capture \NSouthern Asia's resources by force,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.91,0:02:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan had deployed its Combined fleet \Nin the vast waters of Southern Pacific.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.06,0:02:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,According to the Southern strategy, the unit, \Ntasked with protecting the operation's flanks and rear,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.46,0:02:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is the First Mobile Fleet -{https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1st_Air_Fleet}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.96,0:02:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,a large unit of 30 ships, \Nwith 6 aircraft carriers as the core.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.65,0:02:25.72,Sign,,0,0,270,,{\fade(200,300)\c&HFEFDFF&\b1\fs50\blur1\bord0}Episode 1 \N{\fs80}Surprise attack on Pearl Harbor{真珠湾奇襲}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.65,0:02:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,On the fateful day, December 8th, at dawn,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.11,0:02:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the 1st Mobile Fleet carried out \Na secret 5800km expedition,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.88,0:02:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,infiltrating the waters \N360km north of Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.61,0:03:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief, the task force is ready for sortie.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.04,0:03:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I have...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.84,0:03:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,been in charge of getting us all up to here, but now...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.05,0:03:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest is up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.51,0:03:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The latest Intel had arrived. \NEnemy forces anchored at Pearl Harbor are as follows:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.70,0:03:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Battleship - 9, second-class cruiser{乙巡} - 3, \Nseaplane tender{水上機母艦} - 3, destroyer{駆逐艦} - 17.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.91,0:04:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Aircraft carriers and heavy cruisers{重巡} are all dispatched. \NNo abnormal fleet preparations noticed.{unsure what he means, either "the enemy doesn't suspect a thing" or "the fleet is out of military readiness" - lit is "in fleet, abnormal air/mood/atmosphere not registered"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.93,0:04:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The aircraft carrier is not there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.81,0:04:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's Sunday, \Nso it will definitely be back until tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.58,0:04:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Any chance you meet it on your way there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.27,0:04:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If they meet it, they'll have the upper hand.{unsure if this is what he means, maybe its "we have an advantage if we meet it here"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.66,0:04:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But they won't be able to attack Pearl Harbor.{/we won't go to PH then}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.33,0:04:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it matter?{/isn't that fine, too?} \NSinking a carrier would be just as good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.79,0:04:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.71,0:04:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it! Sir, if you excuse me.{/yes, I am going}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.16,0:04:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Counting on you!{/do it properly/take care}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.29,0:04:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If we're spotted by the enemy's carrier while \Nthe attack party is away on the mission, we're screwed.{unsure if it's not "it's not propitious for us to get the attack group getting spotted by enemy kubo after it gets off"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.54,0:04:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Second wave of attack vehicles \Nwould still be here!{lit is "The re-attack force remains" - what does that mean? no se... maybe a reserve forces, maybe a spare group of planes, e.g. preparing for the next sortie?; later this word is reused, there I went with "second wave of attack"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.56,0:04:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This would not be enough.{/this is bad, too} \NWe'll still end up losing some ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.32,0:04:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What did I tell you before?{unsure what he means, lit is "the thing I want to say..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.82,0:04:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Cutting the Gordian Knot!{一刀両断 is taking decisive action; dealing with decisively; cutting the (Gordian) knot​}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.20,0:04:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Precisely! Go there and do what you do best!{/go wild to your heart's content}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.81,0:04:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The first ones to take off \Nare carrier-based fighters of the Zero type. {no clue what is kainin}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.67,0:05:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Also known as Zero Fighters.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.25,0:05:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Equipped with two 20mm machine guns, \Nthis is a maneuverability-focused aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.80,0:05:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Its true power becomes apparent in dog-fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.22,0:05:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the main fighter of the Japanese Navy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.60,0:05:13.81,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H26217B&\blur1\3c&HCECCCB&\fade(0,150)}Victory by all means{勝必}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.47,0:05:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm off!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.24,0:05:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Next goes Nakajima B5N.{/Type 97 carrier-based attack aircraft - 九七式艦上攻撃機}{no clue what is this first word, kaigo?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.66,0:05:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Its job is to carry up to 800 kilograms of torpedoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.47,0:05:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's capable of marching far behind enemy lines. {/its features include boarding/crossing over into the distant enemy camp}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.35,0:05:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This aircraft's article of pride \Nis horizontal bombing accuracy rate of over 50%.{/it boasts its horisontal torpedoing accuracy rate which is always 50% and more}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.69,0:05:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If only I were younger...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.35,0:06:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd fly, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.35,0:06:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Most certainly. In the avant-garde.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.28,0:06:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,6:05, first wave of attack squadron #1 takes off, \Nand at 7:15 already, the second wave will be dispatched.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.89,0:06:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,A total of 350 aircraft, 765 people in them
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.05,0:06:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,congregated into one huge formation in the sky \Nsomewhere in the middle of the Pacific Ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.46,0:06:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, they are preparing \Nto change the course of history.{lit: plunge into history}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.93,0:06:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Among those, the Aichi D3A carrier-based bomber.{again, no clue what is that kaigo}{九九式艦上爆撃機}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.97,0:06:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,During a nose dive, it has an accuracy rate of 80%.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.69,0:06:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Pilots put infinite trust in this model.{/have absolute confidence in its performance.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.04,0:07:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It sure is cloudy up here.{lit: terrible cloud}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.73,0:07:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, by listening to Honolulu broadcast{放送}, \Nwe'll always be up to speed.{unsure what he means and what's that tagutte word, most likely "follow/trace" but still not sure what it means - maybe "we will know everything if we listen to ..." or "in these clouds, we won't lose our way if we fly towards ..."(unlikely)}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.92,0:07:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't suspect a thing. \NPlaying some carefree jazz.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.47,0:07:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, a weather forecast.{why is honolulu radio broadcasting in japanese? fuck if I know}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.49,0:07:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Silence!{/Wait!}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.41,0:07:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Over Oahu, the sky is partly cloudy. \NThe wind blows at about 7.5 km/h.{guess, soku may mean anything, but I found related meanings of "velocity" and "measurement" so I'd assume it's this; also can't hear a thing past "nanaten" - 7-point}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.61,0:07:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, our dear enemies have even been so kind \Nas to tell us the forecast.{lit: enemies-san waiting so hard, they even told us the weather}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.82,0:07:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Cut it out! {I rather hear "shittekure/ittekure" but it makes the following line too perplexing so I have to agree with HA here}You're forgetting \Nthere's still plenty of Japanese living on Hawaii.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.54,0:07:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing useful for us on that radio.{/no reason for us to listen to radio} \NOnly distraction from the hell captain is taking us to.{unsure what he means to say with that whole thing: to taicho-san letting him bring us to the bottom of hell}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.02,0:07:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We're at Oahu.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.84,0:07:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure is a beautiful thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.97,0:07:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Like heaven on earth. \NAlmost makes it a pity to bomb.{/It's a waste to bomb.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.26,0:08:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, we're approaching it! \NAssault formation!{/start attack}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.24,0:08:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The squadron commander just reported back.{/received [something] from captain's plane}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.14,0:08:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,"Tora, tora, tora," isn't it?{/tiger tiger tiger/is attack underway/decided}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.47,0:09:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral{choukan is technically not exactly military title, but "secretary (government); director; chief" however later down this episode, they call every superior this way, regardless of the situation/standing so I'll make it "admiral"}, the captain's plane \Njust transmitted the assault signal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.04,0:09:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.12,0:09:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They've done it. They made it there!{didnt they}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.04,0:09:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,First attack successful!{absolute guess, HA has is "successful attack" and I'm compelled to agree, no clue what is shichu and senko literally has a million meanings}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.30,0:09:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, execute the battle plans \Nthroughout the region!{/quickly start fighting all over the area}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.43,0:09:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, the thunder of war \Nhas been unleashed upon Pacific.{``Hibuta'' means ``a lid that covers the crater of a matchlock gun (of old guns).'' to shoot. This has come to be used in the sense of "starting things, starting action, starting competitions and battles."}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.60,0:09:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is still unaware?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.17,0:09:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Two carriers are nowhere to be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.77,0:09:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Missing, after all? Whatever. We'll be sure to intercept them \Non their way back during the second wave.{lit: if we lure them out now (I think he rather means lure in), we'll definitely hit them during the re-attack (yes, this word again)}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.92,0:09:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Engage!{/shoot}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.13,0:10:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.26,0:11:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you just look at this mess?{/just look at this appearance} \NOur fleet is blown to smithereens!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.93,0:11:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw it. I saw it all. \NI was still in my nightwear when it started.{trusting HA here}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.90,0:11:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Admirals, it is dangerous \Nif you two stay in the same place.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.61,0:11:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Our entire fleet is beheaded \Nif something happens to you!{/who will take command of ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.95,0:11:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, I'll be in my office \Non the opposite side of the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.90,0:11:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Still would you look at what the Japanese did!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.24,0:11:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I will locate our own aircraft carriers \Nand have them chase the enemy away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.78,0:12:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, the anti-aircraft has been suppressed.{no clue what's first word, but sounds close to "ground attack; air-raid" so it must be fighters} \NNow it's naval bombers turn!{lit is rather "sailor bomber"}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.92,0:13:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, first wave had used all its ammo.{either he means "all vehicles in the ... had carried out their duty/shot at the enemy and are now returning" or "... is returning in its entirety/without losses"}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.53,0:13:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Second wave comes in about 30 minutes. \NTake a good picture of the damage.{senka can be both "war; wartime destruction; horrors of war​/war damage; ravages of war; horrors of war" and "battleship" but I think HA tripped over this time}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.04,0:13:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.21,0:14:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,A supposed Japanese parachute unit landing has been but a hoax.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.57,0:14:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, I can't help but appreciate \Nthe enemy's strategy.{/it was a brilliant strategy, even though we are enemies}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.29,0:14:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A sweeping blow.{HA has it "It is a surprise attack." but I think it's rather a "sweep motion" fu for blow and uchi for strike}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.34,0:14:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What's good about "sweeping blow?" This strategy \Nis only used when there's a material advantage. {I think he means "This strategy is only applicable when you are stronger." as if "when the enemy cannot replenish those losses"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.74,0:14:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But now that they've done this, there's no doubt our people \Nwould spare no penny to avenge this treachery.{unsure, lit: we're supposed to use all our provision/taxes in every such case}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.05,0:15:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.53,0:15:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this a Japanese bullet? \NOh, why didn't it pierce my chest as well?{unsure what he means, either it stopped against something in his breast pocket or it didn't hit him at all, just landed in the room?}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.99,0:15:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, I've made sure of the results.{/I've seen the results of battle}\NAll our vehicles returned already.{lit: we have no allies anymore} Turn back, too.{lit: pull back}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.88,0:15:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Jettison that pile of scrap!{/Throw the broken fighter into the sea!}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.77,0:15:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Move it, you idiot! \NSecond wave cannot take off!{/it's in the way of re-attack/second wave}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.98,0:15:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Jettison into the sea anything that clutters the deck!{lit is "scraps/damages" the deck but I think he meant this} \NDon't fret, the sea is warm around here!{/in this area}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.50,0:16:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, emergency landing!{/landing on water - don't know what it is so trusting HA}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.87,0:16:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Attaway.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.00,0:16:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You returned safely! \NHad us all worried here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.40,0:16:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Reporting! Our attacking forces...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.68,0:16:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the results. What are results?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.74,0:16:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yessir! According to my observations, \N4 battleships are sunk, 4 more badly damaged.{https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Attack_on_Pearl_Harbor}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.28,0:16:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So all of them?{zenmetsu is "annihilation; total destruction; complete destruction; crushing defeat"}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.01,0:16:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,All except for Enterprise and Lexington \Nthat weren't present.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.62,0:16:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Aircraft carriers, then?{/all but ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.30,0:16:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So the aircraft carriers survived?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.09,0:17:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We should strike back! \NThey'll be around for 2 or 3 days more!{unsure if this is the meaning but todomatte is " to remain; to abide; to stay (in the one place)​"}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.87,0:17:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say nonsense! \NWe don't have any tankers in the vicinity.{/our tanker would have to come from afar}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.44,0:17:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Think it'll appear here at once,\Njust as we summon it with Morse?{unsure, maybe he means "do you think if we call it with wireless connection, they'll allocate it for us here?"}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.66,0:17:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Their carriers are out of fighting shape!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.37,0:17:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If we manage to get to any of them, even at the expense \Nof revealing ourselves, we've naught to fear!{very unsure, lit: even if we hit at least carrier, and end up revealing address to here to the enemy, we don't have a single thing to fear}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.68,0:17:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So the carriers?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.69,0:17:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral! Each carrier is ready \Nto commence the second wave of attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.90,0:17:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we even go for a second wave?{/is there need for reattack}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.63,0:17:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy will definitely strike{/come} again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.59,0:17:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Our anti-aircraft facilities are prepared now.{unsure if this is what he means, lit is "what's left of counter-attack mechanisms are ready"}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.51,0:17:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there any civilian unrest?{/Are the citizens upset?}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.11,0:17:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,People are utterly disoriented.{/Extremely confused} \NThe radio broadcast could not be continued.{I think he means radio facilities have been damaged and not that they willingly stopped it}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.27,0:17:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What about enemy's carriers?{/then, where are ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.64,0:17:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is supposedly stationed to the south, \Nin the direction of the Wake Island.{/we have concluded they are in the upper southern parts from here - unsure if it's wake island or up there, wake is actually a dedass long way away from and also their carriers headed this way so this would be an extremely stupid thing to surmise, but well}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.12,0:18:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Dispatch the patrol aircraft again.{/release/let out}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.42,0:18:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral, should we deploy it to the north?{/over northern ocean area}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.94,0:18:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming from the south would make a lot more sense.{/the common sense is ...} \NListen, we have to find the Japanese carriers at any cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.80,0:18:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we blow it to pieces.{/smash/crish}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.93,0:18:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What about operational objectives?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.87,0:18:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All are met.{/accomplished}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.21,0:18:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We expect that the American Pacific Fleet won't be able \Nto operate from Pearl Harbor for at least 6 more months.{/won't be able to dispatch/sortie out from ... within next ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.71,0:18:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Our mission of protecting the flanks and the rear \Nof Southern operation{/fleets/gaining a free hand in southern waters}, has been accomplished.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.41,0:18:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We have orders to commence multiple attacks!{/in our orders, the attack should be repeated/reiterated/cycled}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.26,0:18:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We also have the orders to be as cautious as possible, \Nmaking sure the losses are minimized.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.68,0:18:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What of the enemy's condition?{/how is enemy looking}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.98,0:18:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Reports say, the enemy's preparedness for the attack\Nhas been significantly bolstered.{lit: It is estimated that a considerable counterattack ability has been restored.}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.92,0:18:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Our losses in the second wave of attack are 24 planes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.75,0:18:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Next wave would suffer even more losses.{lit is "reattack preparations are not completed" but HA has it "If you re-attack, you have to take the risk."}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.32,0:18:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, the enemy aircraft carrier...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.04,0:19:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go for the night attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.62,0:19:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Just for that purpose, we have a specially trained \Nnight-time torpedo bombing team!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.22,0:19:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you suggesting a gamble?{having to believe HA here as I don't know what he is saying, bakushi is "death from explosion; death from bombing" and I dunno what it means, maybe "so you suggest we wait here like sitting ducks?"}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.52,0:19:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Better than returning \Nwithout playing the trump!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.65,0:19:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Aviation officers!{/Aviation staff.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.53,0:19:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's dangerous to delve too deep \Ninto strategy planning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.53,0:19:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Our goal is to find a balance between attacking \Nin favorable conditions and operating with limited forces.{lit: Consider the balance between the spirit of attack and the limited force.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.99,0:19:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan's industrial capabilities \Nare not meant for mass-producing warships.{/don't allow us to build battleships casually}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.81,0:19:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But the grand-admiral of the Navy wants us \Nto sink as many enemy ships as possible in one go.{/with one stone}{something like the highest possible navy promotion, commander in chief of the total armada}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.39,0:19:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,To the west, the weather is deteriorating.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.44,0:19:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They would be able to take off, \Nbut landing would become increasingly difficult.{lit: for landing, the situation on our side is bad}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.59,0:19:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What can this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.85,0:19:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, we've taken the course \Nto the north-northwest.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.48,0:19:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There won't be any more waves?{/reattack is cancelled}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.06,0:19:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I told them not to call it off. \NDamn it, this is driving me crazy.{unsure what he means lit is "I didn't say cancelled" but I think he means what I wrote}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.09,0:19:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They say admirals are prone to panic attacks.{unsure what he means, lit: a lot of nervous breakdowns in choukan alone}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.27,0:19:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Those guys see airplanes \Nas nothing more than axillary {attacking }force.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.18,0:20:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,All they care about are ships with big guns,{/they only value/prioritize the battleships} \Nblissfully ignorant of the new era about to come.{/they don't understand the times are about to take a big turn}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.07,0:20:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Always so faint-hearted, damn it.{guess, HA has it "that's right" which is obviously not right, I hear doudai sugira iyada - "what about it, too much disgusting" - no clue what it means, maybe "this is too abhorring to me"?}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.12,0:20:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Length of service had gone to their heads.{lit: seniority by length of service to go straight to one's head (of alcohol); to feel the effects (of an illness); to lose one's wits}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.74,0:20:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,If only it was up to Yamaguchi...{unsure what he means, most likely yamaguchi is this lower-rank officer we're seeing right now, can't find any in wikipedia}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.83,0:20:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare an airplane{actually dase is let out/dispatch}! \NI'm going to Headquarters on Akagi.{kikan is "agency; organisation; organization; institution; organ; body" so I think here he means the General Headquarters located on Akagi}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.79,0:20:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain!{abs. guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.65,0:20:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget it, I'll do it myself!{guess, but kasero may be "let me go"} \NI'll talk to the Chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.17,0:20:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me go at once! \NThis is a mutiny! Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.34,0:20:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Japanese army making a landing at Barbers Point \Nturned out to be a false rumor{dema is false rumor (rumour); groundless rumor; misinformation​}.{https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Naval_Air_Station_Barbers_Point}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.89,0:20:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,All we hear is false rumors.{lit: I'm already tired of hearing dema} \NWe're not as scared of actual Japanese army as of rumors.{lit: what's scary now is without japanese army the dema}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.47,0:20:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Soldiers on land report \Ncountless cases of friendly fire.{lit: soldiers shoot how many times at anything that moves}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.06,0:20:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Enterprise sent 17 liaison aircraft, \Nall of which have been shot down.{lit: contact from ..., all 17 planes destroyed}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.05,0:20:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, radar station reports, \Nthe enemy is to the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.07,0:20:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,However, why is there no new wave of attack?{/reattacks stopped coming}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.92,0:20:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Our gasoline tank is still untouched.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.12,0:20:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that they've done it, \Nwe're probably getting withdrawn to San Francisco.{tettai is evacuation; withdrawal; revocation; repeal; retreat}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.23,0:20:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Pearl Harbor waters are shallow. \NThe vessels would be easy to recover.{lit: ships quickly get pulled}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.91,0:20:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This debacle had once again \Nproved battleships obsolete.{lit: by getting sunk, such a wretched ship did seisei - no clue what's this about, maybe "precedent"? because I don't see how the battleships can be deemed guilty for getting sunk in this situation; HA has it "I'm glad that such a rag ship sunk"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.67,0:21:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This will convince even the hardline legislators, whether they like it or not, that the aircraft carriers are the future.{/With this, even the hard-headed lawmakers will admit that the era of naval aircraft has arrived, even if they don't like it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.59,0:21:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The old man will sure be overjoyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.09,0:21:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.26,0:21:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,President Roosevelt.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.05,0:21:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He is a proponent of carriers doctrine, \Nitching to start building them en masse.{/he wants to build many ..., impatient to do it}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.45,0:21:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,After choosing such a strategy, \Nthey don't bring it to completion...{lit: when fighting with an operation like this, they don't pursue it/make doubly sure - I think he means that they didn't go for more waves of attack}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.08,0:21:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Did their commanders lack the guts for it?{/Could it be because their commanders were too craven for this?}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.93,0:21:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is it...{/unless}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.04,0:21:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.60,0:21:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,A trap?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.76,0:21:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Our submarine had located an enemy fleet \Nheading for Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.36,0:21:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Enterprise, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.41,0:21:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Must be. The likelihood of that is very high.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.73,0:21:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a likelihood?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.85,0:21:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We had to rely on a variety \Nof likelihoods to make it here!{lit: didn't we came here betting on chances}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.17,0:21:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Idiot! You strike the iron while it's still hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.54,0:21:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a time to scatter stones \Nand a time to gather them.{HA has it " It is difficult to store the sword in the scabbard." and I think he is right, this is supposed to means something like "it may be hard, but there are times when you just have to sheathe your sword patiently" or "you don't throw fists after the fight is over"}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.10,0:21:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.46,0:22:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral, I have a suggestion.{advice (to a superior); counsel; proposal; suggestion; recommendation} \NOperational objectives have been met.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.03,0:22:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We now lack Intel on the enemy.{/enemy condition is unknown}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.90,0:22:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And due to the bad weather coming our way, \Nour fuel supply is also jeopardized.{HA: Due to bad weather on allies, refueling is also being struck.}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.20,0:22:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I think, it's best that we now return the whole fleet \Nback to Japan safely, while we still can.{HA: I think we should safely return the fleet to Japan now.}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.73,0:22:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The true battlefield for our Imperial Navy \Nlies in the southern waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.00,0:22:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't we take on our enemy \Nin a decisive battle of fleets, fair and square?{HA: Let's show its true value in the fleet decisive battle. - I want to also add "evidential/demonstrative" but I can't find the right word or place}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.92,0:22:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, the Indian Ocean awaits!{ryo is not ocean but I trust HA here}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.30,0:22:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Course{added} to north!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.77,0:22:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,At that moment, there was no one in Akagi high command,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.05,0:22:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,able to predict, with full confidence, \Nwhat would be the effect of further waves of attack.{Lit: that time, hikan (no clue what is it but may be "pessimistic" or "lower government official"), in the akagi surrounding/environment, more reattacks effect, truly sure of it there was nobody}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.80,0:22:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it remains an article of debate to this day, \Nwhether or not the additional waves of attack
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.83,0:22:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,would have changed the course of Pacific War.{/whether or not a re-attack should have been made remains an eternal controversy.}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.00,0:23:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Some accuse them of lacking guts{/criticize for being timid/craven},\Nothers are more discreet and don't throw words around.{/careful and respectful}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.74,0:23:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it is said that a truly talented commander \Nwould never lose sight of his objectives,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.51,0:23:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and is able to take a critical decision \Nwithout batting an eye.{/would come up with a right decision in an instant}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.68,0:23:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Conversely, if you let the situation at hand \Ninfluence your decision at a moment like this, {/on the contrary, if you let emotions take over yourself, losing sight of your objectives,}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.27,0:23:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,no satisfactory result is to be expected \Nafter losing sight of your objective.{/the results can only be expected to be insufficient/inadequate}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.89,0:23:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,0)}The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace.\NBut also bequeathed to us numerous lessons on how to live.{太平洋戦争はわれわれに平和の尊さを教えたがまた生きるための教訓を数多くのこしている}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.29,0:23:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,June 1942.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.96,0:23:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Two major task forces - \NJapanese and American
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.79,0:23:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,spot one another at a measly distance of just 240km, \Nin the Battle of Midway.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.03,0:23:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you approach the opponent's condition, \Nhow do you assess it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.24,0:23:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And how would you fight him?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.30,0:23:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The commanders employ \Nall of their reckoning and intuition.{/The commander puts all of his effort into calculation and judgment.}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.75,0:24:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Deeming conditions favorable,\NAmerica seizes the chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.80,0:24:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as it was about to dispatch its second attack unit, \NJapan's mobile fleet
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.61,0:24:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,has been engulfed \Nin a swarm of American dive bombers.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.97,0:24:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Need just a little more time! \NIf American bomber attack comes at least 5 minutes late,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.62,0:24:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the Battle of Midway \Nwill become another sore spot for them.{very unsure what's this about, アメリカ爆撃機の来襲が遅ければとミッドウェイ海戦に恨みは残る but I don't care since jikai}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.91,0:24:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,However, was this 5 minutes window \Njust a stroke of fate?{/coincidence}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.49,0:24:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War is told to have its own Battle of Sekigahara{https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Sekigahara}, \Nwhich is this one, Battle for Midway.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.38,0:24:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Please witness more of the fateful decisions \Nbeing taken next week.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.89,0:24:39.10,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,300)\c&HF4F4F9&\1a&H18&}{ミッドウェイ海戦(前編)}Animentary: Decision\NEpisode 2 \NBattle of Midway (Part 1){\N Please look forward to it next week}
Comment: 0,0:24:44.42,0:24:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{ch}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.46,0:24:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're a man, let's put your strength to test{男だったら　力を試せ}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.87,0:24:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are a man, keep your hopes burning{男だったら　希望(のぞみ)を燃やせ}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.21,0:24:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are a man, don't lose your heart{男だったら　くじけるな}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.57,0:25:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there's just you and me, a man and a man{俺もおまえも　男と男}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.14,0:25:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Very same bright crimson blood flowing in us both{おなじ真赤な　血が通う}
